===Etymology===
Blended jocular mock-Latin word. Arose in America in the 19th century (about 1837). Probably made up of the following parts: {{etyl|la}} {{term|ab-||away (from)|lang=la}}, (maybe taken from {{etyl|en}} {{term|abscond|lang=en}}), {{etyl|en}} {{term|-ate|lang=en}} (maybe taken from {{etyl|en}} {{term|perambulate|lang=en}}, and the middle portion, "''squatul''", which might be a derivation of {{etyl|en}} {{term|squattle||depart|lang=en}}, or {{term|squat}}.

